4.12	Bhola_Island	Bhola Island	Bhola Island (also called Dakhin Shahbazpur) is the largest island of Bangladesh with an area of 1441 kmÂ². It is situated at the mouth of the Meghna River. It is a district under Barisal Division. There are ferry services from Maju Chowdhury Ghat (Laxmipur district) and from Barisal. Shahbazpur gas field is located in this Island with a proven reserve of 400 mmcft natural gas. The gas is used for running a power station. The road communication of Bhola is good.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/3a/Bangladesh_location_map.svg/240px-Bangladesh_location_map.svg.png
